    # Generate a random value for each feature respecting their distributions and correlations
    target_thickness = rng.uniform(*target_thickness_range)
    pulse_width = rng.integers(*pulse_width_range, endpoint=True)
    energy = max(rng.normal(energy_mean, np.sqrt(2*energy_variance))  # sqrt variance for normal distribution
    spot_size = rng.uniform(*spot_size_range)
    intensity = max(min(intensity_mean + (rng.random() * (intensity_max - intensities_mean), intensities_min) # Adjusting within the range and variance

    # Intensity and Power are highly positively correlated with Energy, hence influence is modeled here directly using their Spearman correlation

    cutoff_energy = max(cutoff_energy_mean, min(intensities_min, energy))  # Cutoff Energy is influenced by Intensity but also has a lower bound related to Minimum value

    return [target_material, target_thickness, pulse_width, energy, spot_size, intensity, power, cutoff_energy]
